spanGrp.span: The Serengeti district in the Mara region
Wilaya ya serengeti mkoa wa Mara
The time when I was growing up
When I grew up, I saw,
gwalanheek nyas gegurs geyet aa gefk eftaad aa
The elders called each other to sit down
aa qamn gad eyak gurgwagudig gika
And now there aren't these groups anymore
Na sasa kuna vikao hayo tena
qay gehetu aa gey gwand ee
In the old days we were saying they were there
Each person is following their own mind
Kila mtu anafuata akili yake mwenyewe
And the time to marry, if it comes
Na muda wa kuoa kama imefika
gibalool aa qondang' gidab aniin gaheedoj gagasay dageshi
You speak with your father, that "I want to grow up, I want to marry"
Unaongea na baba yako kwamba mimi nimekua nataka nioe
gobarany fug quwaar aa gobaloolj much
You understand each other and you speak well
Mnaelewana ninyi wa nyumbani na mnaongea vizuri
You are permitted to go and marry
You go to find a spouse
ira qamn aa asees aa gegenay nadeeg
But now we have married into different tribes
The Datooga aren't here, they have become very few
ee gesoolay nadeeg gichay iyiid qwayam balool quwaar
We have just married into tribes, if the person comes they change their home language
Tumeoa makabila tu akija tu anageuza lugha ya nyumbani
Because now the women they are managing things
If you marry then you follow their language
Ukioa tu unafuata lugha ya kwao
hanan gid qamn gosawaneesa law hiji
It is something that is hurting us here in Law
Ndiyo kitu kilichootuumiza sisi wa musoma
You have become a person of a different tribe
aa guwas asimjand gequs aa eronyeew gwalanyeek obalool much
And you are an Asimjeeg until you meet with the elders, speak well to them
Na wewe ni mwasimjega mpaka ukutane na wazee mwongee vizuri
You ask ask them "Your youth, where are they?"
isifk eparsiineneen gid quwar mad nal
If you come to be asked in the native tongue you don't know
But here we are still participating
The people in the west have been destroyed
aa iqus ng'asheeg ga wet gegeet gad eweta geyeet
And if you say something about help, we still help each other
Na ukisema kwa mambo ya msaada bado tunasaidiana
ngvasheeg ga ee barood ng'any nyas gelulj geyet musaada
For farming we often invite each other to help
Kwa habari ya kilimo huwa tunaalikana msaada
We go to the fields to help each other
qay asees gehetu abij aa geyagay marebajeeg
In the old days we ate a certain kind of food
Zamani sisi tulikua hapo na tunakula chakula aina fulani
aa geng'atiid ng'adood gating barood gab ee gating'
And we farmed by hand, hand farming
Na tunalima kwa kilimo cha mikono kilimo ni ya mikono
And now cattle can be obtained
ndo maan qamn nyees geluul geyeet aa barood gang'isch dugw
That means that now often we are inviting each other and the ones working are the cows.
'Ndiyo maana sasa huwa tunaalikana na wanaolima ni ng''ombe'
My story, I think it will be like this.
